entry.title: Font face font requests no longer flood dev tools
entry.content:
`EmulateLoadStartedForInspector` gets called whenever

@font-face rules are processed by StyleResolver/StyleEngine. `cached_resources_map_` is checked to see whether or not

the inspector emulation should occur; however, it does not get

updated once the emulation is done. This has the potential

to cause a flood of font requests to show up in DevTools.



To fix this, we will create a new map that tracks on when a given resource is emulated and ensure that the same resource doesn't get emulated multiple times.



Test: see crbug.com/1502591 for more details on the test

scenario

entry.title: Allow createEncodedStreams on PCs without encodedInsertableStreams param
entry.content:
Allow creating Encoded Transforms for any Receivers and Senders, so

long as createEncodedStreams() is called by JS synchronously after

sender/receiver creation. This is achieved by setting up a WebRTC

transform on all transceivers, but "short circuiting" it if JS hasn't

set up its own transform within an event loop spin of creation. This

will make the transform just pass frames to be transformed directly back

without invoking the cost of a thread hop or any JS work.



The existing behaviour (dropping all frames until a JS transform is

installed) is preserved for PCs created with {encodedInsertableStreams:

true}.



This implements the algorithm defined in https://www.w3.org/TR/2023/WD-webrtc-encoded-transform-20231012/#stream-creation,

but for the Chromium createEncodedStreams() method, improving

conformance incrementally.

entry.title: pip: Control lifecycle of PipController with window visibility
entry.content:
This change fixes several crashes in `PipController` by chainging

the lifecycle so that `pip_window_` is updated in response to

window visibility changes instead of window existence changes.



The primary reason for this is that an ash-chrome PiP window doesn't

get destroyed when it gets killed (e.g. with the close button).

As long as the original web page is alive, the PiP window remains as

hidden and will be reused when PiP gets activated again on the same

page. This confusing behavior is causing the following concrete

issues:



(i) As `pip_window_` in `PipController` is only updated with window

state or existence changes, currently the proper PiP window may

not be set to `PipController` in some cases. For example, after

ash-chrome PiP -> ARC PiP -> ash-chrome PiP are shown in this

order, `pip_window_` in `PipController` becomes null although PiP

is active.



(ii) Callers of `PipController::UpdatePipBounds()` easily forgets to

check the visibility of the PiP window they find by iterating

through all windows. This is problematic especially in combination

with the problem (i) above because invoking

`PipController::UpdatePipBounds()` when `pip_window_` causes a

crash.



To resolve this confusion, with this change, `pip_window_` in

`PipController` gets updated with window visibility changes. This

way, `pip_window_` only becomes non-null when PiP is actually active

(v.s. a PiP window exists in the system regardless of its

visibility).



For (ii), this change also replaces the `CHECK(pip_window_)` with

an if statement because it's difficult to ensure that all callers

don't forget to take the visibility of PiP in consideration.



Bug: b/309498856

Test: Manually went though all the PiP CUJ with ash-chrome, ARC,

and Lacros, verified no crash happened.

entry.title: [sync] Avoid unnecessary call to StopAndClear()
entry.content:
No expected user-visible behavioral changes, although technically it's

hard to claim there aren't behavioral changes strictly speaking as

SyncServiceObserver functions are exercised differently.



This call, introduced long ago in

https://codereview.chromium.org/14691004, shouldn't be necessary

anymore (with the exception of custom/explicit passphrase users, more

on this below):

1) For Ash, the code is unreachable because

IsInitialSyncFeatureSetupComplete() always returns true since

https://crrev.com/c/4882503.

2) Outside Ash, the code is only reachable if

IsInitialSyncFeatureSetupComplete() is false: in this case revoking

the Sync ConsentLevel leads to SyncEngine being reconfigured into

transport mode. There is no known reason that requires

StopAndClear() being invoked, barring explicit passphrase users.



For users with explicit passphrase (custom passphrase and frozen

implicit passphrase), the call continues to be necessary to avoid a

user-facing behavioral change: if the user entered the passphrase

while setup was ongoing, canceling this setup clears the passphrase.



The change is motivated by the need to redesign or remove

SyncService::StopAndClear().

entry.title: [ThumbnailCapturerMac] Restrict the number of capture calls in flight
entry.content:
In certain situations, such as if the screen is locked, we may end up

calling [SCScreenshotManager captureImageWithFilter] without receiving

any callbacks with thumbnails. We may even try to capture the same

window multiple times. The capture calls are put in a queue and we

suspect that there's a crash in an OS component if too many capture

calls are in flight simultaneously.



This CL limits the number of outstanding calls in two ways:



- A window is not put in the capture queue again until we've received

a callback from the capturer.

- The number of capture calls in flight is limited to the same number

as the maximum number of sources to capture per refresh cycle.

entry.title: [MO/BRP] TypeTraits: set default RawPtrTraits per type
entry.content:
- Add `base::raw_ptr_traits::kTypeTraits`

- This is a type trait to associate type `T` with `RawPtrTraits`.

- It is `kEmpty` by default.

- Users may declare specialization of it to change default traits for

`T`.

- Rename some compile-constant RawPtrTraits in `raw_ptr`/`raw_ref`.

- Existing RawPtrTraits, specified by second template argument of

pointer types, is renamed to `PointerTraits`.

- New `Traits` is union of `PointerTraits` and type-based traits.



Context:

We want to add some more safety checks to BRP whose pointee is

annotated with AMS macro. However, PA is designed to be standalone

library, so we cannot refer to the macro directly.

`kTypeTraits` makes it possible to change BRP's behavior

from outside PA, without making direct dependency.

We will implement these additional safety checks as a separate CL,

and the checks should be triggered by some new RawPtrTraits.

Then the macro can add the RawPtrTraits through `kTypeTraits`.

entry.title: [MO] Remove LightweightQuarantine's metadata management
entry.content:
- Currently `LightweightQuarantine` is responsible has two

functionalities:

- Defer `Free()` request to quarantine an object

- Record `Free()`-time information

- This CL drops support of `Free()`-time information for more

flexibility.

- `LightweightQuarantineBranch` owns a list of deferred `Free()`

requests. It still requires locking, but thanks to separation we can

have one branch for one thread, meaning that it requires no lock

when used like that.

- `LightweightQuarantineRoot` is glue for

`LightweightQuarantineBranch`es.

It holds some stats and configuration for the quarantine system.

entry.title: [OOPIF PDF] Reorder PostTask() calls in plugin throttle code
entry.content:
When PluginResponseInterceptorURLLoaderThrottle::WillProcessResponse()

is handling a PDF with the OOPIF PDF feature enabled, it must schedule

events such that PdfViewerStreamManager creation and setup completes

before the throttled URL is allowed to resume loading via ResumeLoad().



Currently, the order is backwards, and as such, PdfViewerStreamManager

creation races against network events. Reorder the calls in

WillProcessResponse(), such that PdfViewerStreamManager creation always

happens before ResumeLoad(). With the correct ordering,

https://crrev.com/1229550 can safely reland.



Bug: 1445746

entry.title: Replace vector<display::GammaRampRGBEntry> with display::GammaCurve
entry.content:
This should have no functional changes.



By using the display::GammaCurve::Sample function we can simplify

the code that sends the LUTs that are sent to DRM (resampling directly

in place and not having to special case the identity function unless

desired).



This will also allow us to transparently support parametric transfer

functions (which are often specified in display color profiles).



This will also allow us to be more intentional about the different

gamma curves that will be specified (those for a color profile

versus those for adjusting brightness as in the chromecast usage).



Bug: 1505062

> we preserves the current behavior if Page Colors is 'Off' and forced
